## SOLID and DRY Principles

### Single Responsibility (SRP)
- Controllers: only handle HTTP (parse request, delegate to service, format response)
- Services: only orchestrate business logic
- Repositories: only handle persistence
- Validators: only validate, never persist

### Open/Closed (OCP)
- Add new behavior through new adapters, not by modifying domain code
- Example: add a new payment provider by implementing `IPaymentGateway`, not by modifying the domain service

### Dependency Inversion (DIP)
```typescript
// Good: depends on interface
@Injectable()
export class CandidateService {
  constructor(
    @Inject(CANDIDATE_REPOSITORY)
    private readonly candidateRepository: ICandidateRepository,
  ) {}
}

// Bad: depends on concrete class
export class CandidateService {
  private repo = new MongoCandidateRepository(); // never do this
}
```

