## API Design Standards

### REST Endpoints
- Use nouns, not verbs: `/candidates` not `/getCandidates`
- Plural resource names: `/candidates`, `/positions`
- Nested resources for relationships: `/positions/:id/candidates`
- HTTP methods: `GET` (read), `POST` (create), `PUT` (full update), `PATCH` (partial update), `DELETE`

### Response Patterns
- Mutations always return a consistent envelope:
  ```json
  { "message": "Candidate created successfully", "data": { } }
  ```
- List endpoints must support pagination:
  ```json
  { "data": [], "metadata": { "total": 100, "page": 1, "limit": 10, "totalPages": 10 } }
  ```

### NestJS Controller Example
```typescript
@Controller('candidates')
@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)
export class CandidateController {
  constructor(private readonly candidateService: CandidateService) {}

  @Get(':id')
  async findById(@Param('id') id: string): Promise<CandidateResponseDto> {
    return this.candidateService.findById(id);
  }

  @Post()
  @HttpCode(201)
  async create(@Body() dto: CreateCandidateDto): Promise<CreateCandidateResponseDto> {
    return this.candidateService.create(dto);
  }
}
```

